Why This Happens

Example CSS like this causes the issue:

.sidebar .active {
    border-left: 4px solid blue;
    padding-left: 10px;
}

Other items:

.sidebar a {
    padding-left: 14px;
}

So when active → extra border + padding changes width, making the item move.

Correct Fix (Best Solution)

Keep the same spacing for all sidebar items, even when inactive.

CSS Fix
.sidebar a {
    display: block;
    padding: 10px 15px;
    border-left: 4px solid transparent;
}

.sidebar a.active {
    border-left: 4px solid #3b82f6;
    background-color: #f3f6ff;
}

Now the border space always exists, so items won't shift.

Example Sidebar HTML
<div class="sidebar">

<a href="/unverified" class="active">
☐ Unverified Users
</a>

<a href="/verified">
☐ Verified Users
</a>

<a href="/inactive">
☐ Deleted / Inactive Users
</a>

</div>
Alternative Fix (Bootstrap Style)

If using Bootstrap:

.nav-link {
    padding-left: 20px;
}

.nav-link.active {
    border-left: 4px solid blue;
}

Add placeholder border:

.nav-link {
    border-left: 4px solid transparent;
}
